text: (church bell ringing)

- [Vilija] We are witnessing
a very quick advancement
of technology in different fields,
and there is going to be a need
for more and more female leaders.
(gentle music)
I am Vilija Vainaite,
I'm an AWS AI and ML Scholarship student,
and currently living in the Netherlands.

I'm hoping to become a role
model one day and empower women

who have an interest in
technology to pursue it further.
(gentle music continues)

- Hello.
- Hi
- Vaá¹‡akkam.
- I'm from Nairobi, Kenya.
- I'm from Himachal Pradesh, India.

- I'm interested in
artificial intelligence.
- If they can do it, then I can do it too.
- [Dancer] Go to the left first?
(people speaking faintly)
- So I do the opposite that you do.
- Yeah, so you have to do it like this.
(light music)

- [Vilija] Music has followed
me throughout my whole life.
I started music school at seven years old.
(piano music)
I remember my piano teacher saying

that playing the piano is
like solving a math problem.
It's not necessarily about memorizing
how a part of code looks like,

or how a part of music
piece should be played,

but more about understanding
the pattern behind it.
I grew up in Vilnius, Lithuania.
(ethereal music)
Back in Lithuania,

I saw a lot of female
leaders in different fields,
including technology field.

My grandma went on to work
in information technology
and my mother is a Supreme Court justice.
They showed me that hard work
and perseverance can get you very far.

I am finishing my master's in
Crisis and Security Management

at Leiden University
here in the Netherlands,
focusing on researching the impact

of artificial intelligence
and cybersecurity.
(fast tempo music)
The AWS AI and ML Scholarship program

gave me the opportunity to work
with machine learning models
and understand them from the backend.

Thanks to the program,
I was able to understand
how is actually AI used
in cybersecurity offense and defense.

I'm really passionate
about using that knowledge,

and finally put that all together
in the professional field.
When I came to the Netherlands,

I felt that there was
really a big disparity
between genders in the workforce.

That's why I wanted to
get involved in it myself

and create a difference
here in the Netherlands.
(dissonant music)

I found some teammates
and we officially created
the Women4Cyber the Netherlands Chapter.

We hope to help women
realize their potential
in cybersecurity and show it is possible

to become a female leader
in a technical field.

In the future, I will be
working as a consultant

improving the resilience 
of organizations.

I'm really passionate about
working towards humane
and ethical technology solutions
and making AI work to our benefit.
